Goal:
Add objective terms that compare internal Flux image-conditioning / transformer hidden representations between:
1. original input and perturbed input, if accessible before generation
2. original diffusion run and perturbed diffusion run, if accessible during generation

The purpose is anti-edit/deepfake prevention:
Make the input look normal, but disrupt Flux’s internal processing enough that the edit fails, degrades, changes structure, or changes identity.

